text: Lee Hye-young (born 30 July 1982) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in flyweight at the 2001 World Taekwondo Championships in Jeju City, and a bronze medal in bantamweight at the 2011 World Taekwondo Championships in Gyeongju. She won a gold meda at the 2006 Asian Taekwondo Championships in Bangkok. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
